The / means the path is the entire server
Use the permission properties:
-user
-group
Also the size property -size
Tip: Use 2>/dev/null to clear out the permission denied ones so you can see the password one clearly.
The number 2 stands for standard error
The > stands for redirecting the output from the left to the right side
The /dev/null is basically the black hole or trash can, so all those permission denied messages get deleted.
